y cases. A bold intervention in legal and anthropological scholarship, this book is a timely consideration of an urgent issue facing Indigenous communities worldwide and the courts hearing their cases.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEvidence (Law)zCanada. 0aIndians of North AmericaxLegal status, laws, etczCanada. 0aIndigenous peoplesxLegal status, laws, etczCanada. 0aInuitxLegal status, laws, etczCanada. 0aOral traditionzCanada. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Native American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010z978311127414008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010z978311127721908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077482072140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774820721423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774820721/original  a978-3-11-127414-0  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2011-2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-127721-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2011 - 2010c2010d2011  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles